{"word":"H3715 - כְּפִיר - kᵉphîyr - kef-eer' - Lion","slug":"H3715","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">כְּפִיר</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>kᵉphîyr"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>kef-eer'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Lion"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05DB;&#x05BC;&#x05E4;&#x05D9;&#x05E8; - k<sup>e</sup>ph&#x0131;&#x0302;yr</b> - <i>kef-eer'</i><p/>From <a href=\"#/H3722\">H3722</a>; a <i>village</i> (as <i>covered</i> in by walls); also a young <i>lion</i> (perhaps as <i>covered</i> with a mane): - (young) lion, village. Compare <a href=\"#/H3723\">H3723</a>."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H3716\">H3716</a>, <a href=\"#/H3723\">H3723</a>, <a href=\"#/H3724\">H3724</a>, <a href=\"#/H3726\">H3726</a>"}]}